WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.200 --> 00:00:01.468
A family in Taiwan received 

00:00:01.468 --> 00:00:03.203
a LINE message from their father.

00:00:03.203 --> 00:00:04.404
"I had a mountain incident. 

00:00:04.404 --> 00:00:06.072
Please report for rescue."

00:00:06.072 --> 00:00:07.440
"Xi Luan Da Shan."

00:00:07.807 --> 00:00:08.775
Then nothing.

00:00:08.775 --> 00:00:10.009
His phone went silent.

00:00:10.744 --> 00:00:13.012
But it said nothing about where exactly. 

00:00:13.079 --> 00:00:15.448
No GPS coordinates. No landmark.

00:00:15.448 --> 00:00:17.117
No distance along the trail.

00:00:17.317 --> 00:00:18.485
Just the mountain name.

00:00:19.085 --> 00:00:21.054
That is a very large area.

00:00:22.055 --> 00:00:24.090
learn how to send your GPS coordinates

00:00:24.090 --> 00:00:24.891
in an emergency. 

00:00:25.091 --> 00:00:25.992
It is simple.

00:00:25.992 --> 00:00:27.761
Four decimal points is enough.

00:00:28.061 --> 00:00:31.264
That one message could have saved the search teams days. 

00:00:31.631 --> 00:00:34.200
Your phone already knows exactly where you are.

00:00:34.200 --> 00:00:36.569
The problem is — nobody else does.

00:00:36.803 --> 00:00:38.405
He kept going downhill. 

00:00:38.405 --> 00:00:40.907
That is the instinct — find a way out. 

00:00:41.007 --> 00:00:42.709
But that is always wrong. 

00:00:42.709 --> 00:00:43.610
On terrain like this,

00:00:43.610 --> 00:00:45.412
going downhill randomly almost

00:00:45.412 --> 00:00:47.447
always leads to a WATERFALL.

00:00:47.447 --> 00:00:48.581
Or a CLIFF.

00:00:48.748 --> 00:00:50.216
There is no safe way down 

00:00:50.216 --> 00:00:52.051
except the trail you came from.

00:00:52.118 --> 00:00:53.219
The wall under the waterfall

00:00:53.219 --> 00:00:55.021
is over one hundred meters high.

00:00:55.188 --> 00:00:56.423
He fell twenty meters

00:00:56.423 --> 00:00:57.824
onto the first ledge.

00:00:58.224 --> 00:01:00.260
Located two hundred fifty meters

00:01:00.260 --> 00:01:02.562
below the ridge with the main trail.

00:01:03.163 --> 00:01:04.964
The mountains will always be there. 

00:01:04.964 --> 00:01:07.200
Be ready when you go.

